Qardio, Inc. is an American technology company that specializes in heart health monitoring products. It was founded by Marco Peluso and Rosario Iannella in early 2012, after Peluso's father suffered a stroke.
Qardio's first product, QardioArm, is a wireless blood pressure monitor that connects with Apples's Health app, received FDA 510K clearance in June 2014.
At CES 2015, Qardio announced two new products, QardioBase – smart scale and body analyzer and QardioMD – a medical dashboard for doctors. QardioBase became available for sale in November 2015.
Qardio launched the second generation of its smart scale, Qardio Base 2 in September 2017 
QardioCore ambulatory ECG/EKG monitor received CE Mark in August 2017 


